text.tspan: Share of population suffering from mental or substance use disorders, males
Share of males vs. females suffering from any mental health or substance use disorders; this includes depression, anxiety,
bipolar, eating disorders, alcohol or drug use disorders, and schizophrenia. This share has been age-standardized assuming a
constant age structure to compare prevalence between countries and through time.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
